als. But its own story also provides a fascinating case study of film industry management during one of the most vexing periods in American social history. RKO Radio Pictures: A Titan is Born offers a vivid history of a thirty-year roller coaster of unstable finances, management battles, and artistic gambles. Richard Jewell has used unparalleled access to studio documents generally unavailable to scholars to produce the first business history of RKO, exploring its decision-making processes and illuminating the complex interplay between art and commerce during the heyday of the studio system. Behind the blockbuster films and the glamorous stars, the story of RKO often contained more drama than any of the movies it ever produced.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  a1930s hollywood.  a20th century hollywood.  aamerican cinema.  aamerican film history.  aastaire rogers musicals.  ablockbuster films.  acitizen kane.  aclassic era.  aclassic films.  aclassic hollywood.  afamous hollywood studios.  afilm criticism.  afilm fans.  afilm industry history.  afred astaire.  agolden age hollywood.  agunga din.  ahistory of cinema.  ahollywood stars.  ahollywood studio history.  ahoward hughes.  akatharine hepburn.  aking kong.  amovie buff books.  amovie fanatic books.  amovie lovers books.  aorson welles.  astudio production history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052027179140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095195240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520951952423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520951952/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c20